    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Dr. Beverly Hall has been running the Newark schools since July, when the state took them over. Her boss, Education Commissioner Leo F. Klagholz, is ready to name her Superintendent through June 1999 and remove the "acting" from her title. Last night, he told the local advisory board about his recommendation, which must be approved by the State Board of Education, according to Peter Peretzman, a spokesman for the Board of Education..</p>
      </block>
